The paper proposes a deep neural network model for non-stationary data streams, which falls under the category of machine learning. Specifically, the model is based on stochastic configuration networks, which is a type of feedforward neural network. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed method on benchmark datasets, which suggests a focus on data science and data mining, leading to the inclusion of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a way to grow and shrink the structure of the deep network autonomously from data streams, which could be considered a form of self-organization and could fall under the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
